cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a generic approach to enhance their resistance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of learning algorithms and data transformation, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
